<TITLE> Mauritius 2007 tourism earnings up 27 percent </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PORT LOUIS, Feb 8 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Mauritius' tourism earnings rose 27 percent to 40.6 billion Mauritius rupees ($1.4 billion) in 2007 from 31.9 billion rupees the year before, top daily newspaper L'Express reported on Friday. "The revenues were 40.6 billion rupees which represents an increase of 8.7 billion rupees over 2006, a growth of 27.2 percent," the daily quoted tourism minister Xavier-Luc Duval as saying at a tourism workshop. The sector is key for the roughly $7 billion Indian Ocean economy, expected to grow 6 percent this year. Jean-Michel Pitot, president of the nation's association of hoteliers and restaurant owners (AHRIM), told the workshop Mauritius was targeting 990,000 tourists in 2008, up 10 percent on the 900,000 visitors last year. Construction of new hotel rooms, greater room occupancy during the low season, and more efficient use of the Internet would all contribute, he said. Mauritius aims to receive 2 million tourists by 20
